! ospfd configuration for node {{NODE_ID}}
hostname {{NODE_ID}}
!
! Every link is a /30 between exactly two routers, so each interface is treated as
! point-to-point: this skips broadcast DR election (and its wait timer), letting
! adjacencies reach Full and reconverge within the test's convergence budget. Fast
! hello/dead timers keep failure detection well under convergence_timeout_ms.
{{OSPF_INTERFACES}}
router ospf
 ospf router-id {{ROUTER_ID}}
 redistribute connected
 ! Fast SPF and LSA timers. The default MinLSInterval (5s) and SPF max-hold (5s)
 ! mean a rapidly flapping link exhausts its LSA re-origination budget: the final
 ! "link-up" Router-LSA is suppressed and never re-triggered, so SPF keeps routing
 ! around a link whose adjacency is actually Full. Shrinking the throttles lets the
 ! restored link be re-advertised and recomputed within the convergence budget.
 timers throttle spf 0 50 200
 timers throttle lsa all 50
 timers lsa min-arrival 50
{{OSPF_NETWORKS}}
!
line vty
!
